in the fifth with a two-run homer.  St. Louis starter Chris Carpenter got the win, allowing two
runs on five hits in six innings, and five Cardinals relievers
combined for three scoreless innings. C.J. Wilson, the first of
four Texas pitchers, took the loss.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
